Box Model : 
Box Model simply defines how Html elements are going to be laid out on browser or output screen. Box Model contains three main properties : 
a. Margin
b. Border
c. Padding

a. Margin : 
    i. Margin have no color
    ii.Implements outside the box or elements
    iii. properties : 
            margin-top : 10px; 
            margin-right : 20px; 
            margin-bottom : 30px; 
            margin-left : 40px;

            shorthand way : 
            margin : 10px 20px 30px 40px;
                      T    R    B    L 
                      
            margin : 10px 20px 30px;
                      T   R L   B

            margin : 10px 20px;            
                     T B   R L 

            margin : 10px;
                     TRBL

    b. Border : 
    i. Border have color
    ii.Implements outside the box or elements
    iii. properties : 
            border-top : 10px; 
            border-right : 20px; 
            border-bottom : 30px; 
            border-left : 40px;

            shorthand way : 
            border : 10px 20px 30px 40px;
                      T    R    B    L 
                      
            border : 10px 20px 30px;
                      T   R L   B

            border : 10px 20px;            
                     T B   R L 

            border : 10px;
                     TRBL

    c. Padding : 
    i. Padding do not have color
    ii.Implements inside the box or elements
    iii. properties : 
            padding-top : 10px; 
            padding-right : 20px; 
            padding-bottom : 30px; 
            padding-left : 40px;

            shorthand way : 
            padding : 10px 20px 30px 40px;
                      T    R    B    L 
                      
            padding : 10px 20px 30px;
                      T   R L   B
            padding : 10px 20px;            
                     T B   R L 
            padding : 10px;
                     TRBL